CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 14, 1959, pg. A3, reads: "Large Room - More than 200 Masons, together with more than 200 members and friends of Loendi, gathered in this area, as indoor ceremonies were conducted. The space, when completed will be the main dining room of the club, and will also serve as a banquet hall, ballroom and general assembly. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Man wearing eyeglasses and suit, standing with arms behind back, behind table with Loendi Club brochures, and speaking in microphone to crowd of standing women and men, in Loendi Club for cornerstone laying ceremonies
